claim: Quinoa is in the amaranth family.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Atriplex hortensis , also known as garden orache , red orach , mountain spinach , French spinach , or simply orache or arrach , is a Eurasian species of plant in the amaranth family  (  for many years classified in the goosefoot family , now absorbed in the amaranth family  )  .

claim: Quinoa is in the amaranth family.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Quinoa  (  -LSB- ˈkiːnwɑː -RSB- or -LSB- kɪˈnoʊ.ə -RSB- , from Quechua kinwa or kinuwa  )  is the common name for Chenopodium quinoa , a flowering plant in the amaranth family Amaranthaceae .
